From: Sagi Grimberg <sagi@grimberg.me>
Date: Wed, 29 Mar 2017 20:54:46 +0300
Subject: nvme-fc: increment request retries counter before requeuing
References: bsc#1037838
Git-commit: f2cd54d3eba3a2048edcb91f145336180c55aee5
Patch-Mainline: v4.7

This way our max retry limit holds as well.

Signed-off-by: Sagi Grimberg <sagi@grimberg.me>
Reviewed-by: Max Gurtovoy <maxg@mellanox.com>
Reviewed-by: Christoph Hellwig <hch@lst.de>
Signed-off-by: Jens Axboe <axboe@fb.com>
Signed-off-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
---
 drivers/nvme/host/fc.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/nvme/host/fc.c b/drivers/nvme/host/fc.c
index 0e5bb3c..ad6f9bf 100644
--- a/drivers/nvme/host/fc.c
+++ b/drivers/nvme/host/fc.c
@@ -1980,6 +1980,7 @@ nvme_fc_complete_rq(struct request *rq)
 
 	if (unlikely(rq->errors)) {
 		if (nvme_req_needs_retry(rq, rq->errors)) {
+			rq->retries++;
 			nvme_requeue_req(rq);
 			return;
 		}
